		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=1286"><span id=Encyclopedia>gbaji</span></a><b><span id=Encyclopedia><br>Encyclopedia</span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*"/><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*"/><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />9757 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Good [4.02]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=gbaji&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Different strokes for different folks I suppose. It's not that we love getting killed. It *is* a challenge, in the way that without the risk of death the game wouldn't be very challenging.<br><br>Honestly, the best thing to do when you die is just get right back into your group and keep going. At the lower levels of the game, the gear mudflation and ready availablity of buffs makes regaining exp super easy. Imagine hunting where you are in purely oldworld gear. Heck. I remember when you were &quot;uber&quot; if you had all bronze armor by the time you were level 20. And armor with stats on it? You had to raid for that stuff. A level 35 character was happy as anything to get a piece of armor with +3str on it (and nothing else!). I'm not kidding.<br><br>You're fighting the same mobs with 5 times better gear. Yeah. That doesn't make you immune to death, but it sure should make it easier to recover. Don't sweat not getting rezzes. I don't think I recieved a single rez on my first character until he was well into his 30s. I'm always amazed at folks in their 20s standing around begging for rezzes for 30 minutes at a time, when they could have gotten the exp back in 10.<br><br>By the time you actually lose something significant from dying in terms of time, rezzes are pretty much available easily. CRs are never fun (makes DoN worth it right there IMO!), but not that difficule ultimately. Try dying in your mid teens at the bottom of befallen sometime. That was a &quot;fun&quot; CR (and probably the hardest I've ever had, not counting some early fear raids).<br><br>Dying sucks. No doubt about it. But it's just part of the game.</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from San Diego, CA</td></tr></table>
